ferent than when you're attacking the other charachter. Additions would be great.. since i've not been jumped by alot of classes..<br>
<br>
Druid - <br>
    If snare resists, just stay on him.. always swing around back for the BS when it lands... if snare does stick.. then.. you should either follow after him slowly with throwing items.. or wait till he sits down to med.. hide/sneak.. hope he loses targeting.. and then either bind wound, or go around back for the backstab.  Oh, dots.. gotta hate 'em.. but with these guys.. if you get them to low health.. you might be able to die from a dot, and save your coin/item... (happened to me once.. i was thrilled =)<br>
<br>
Wizard -<br>
    If the inital root lands, then sorry.. you're dead, unless you have some pumice on you.  If not, then stick on him.. dont let him leave your attack range.. and worry more about interrupting his spells than about backstabbing.. save your backstab for when you see &quot;a wizard beings to cast a spell&quot;... and.. if you think you can pull it off.. go around back and backstab.. if not.. just hit the button so it interrupts him.<br>
<br>
Mage -<br>
    Well, still havent been jumped by an earth pet and lived to tell about it... havent ever been jumped by a mage without an earth pet up.. so..... not sure about that one =\<br>
<br>
Necro -<br>
    Same as druid.. with the added annoyance factor of the pet..... life taps........... etc<br>
<br>
Enchanter -<br>
    Whoop-t-doo.. you've got yourself a doosy here.  You will most likely be blind, mezzed, debuffed, and possibly whirled before you get a chance to do anything.  If you have pumice, dont be afraid to use it.  When you wake up out of your dazed/debuffed slumber... go straight for him.. once again.. save your backstab for the interrupt.  The enchanter has alot of stuns that he/she can use to just get rid of you for a while with.  Kind of a hard one to win here.... Also have very low hp, and Rune.... cursed rune.<br>
<br>
Rogue and Warrior -<br>
   If you're being jumped by one of these, they're probably extremely twinked, or have a friend hideing behind a bush with a baseball bat.  If this is the case, run.  If not, try to stay out of jousting.. mix up your routine.. circle strafe for the backstab as SOON as it recycles..<br>
<br>
Paladin or Cleric -<br>
   Blind, nuke, melee.  Thats basically their strategy.  Paladins can melee better than the cleric, but the cleric does everything else better.  Just be carefull here, if you get to 2 bubbles, just run.. they will have a hard time killing you, or rooting you(if you have a decent MR)..<br>
<br>
SK -<br>
   Treat like a warrior, but remember.. they have harmtouch.. so they could really really hurt you really really quickly. They usually start off with their flashy spells... hopefully darkness resists.  Even if it does, the guy is still going to run at you and start jousting.  They often carry big weapons.. so they will just run up.. smack.. and run away.  Very annoying.  Just get away if the snare dosnt resist.  If it does... try to avoid their big weapons.<br>
<br>
Others -<br>
   Dont have any experience with them... not sure what i missed... if anyone has any suggestions.. it'd be very very helpfull to all of us.... hope this saves at least one rogue's &quot;uber-phat-lewt&quot;.<br>
<br>
