Pray you resist those dots, and just stick on them. If they are dotting you, you can bind wound as only spells with a dd component to them will break bind wound. Try to BS when applicable, but you might want to save it as a bonus attack if you have slower weapons.<br>
<br>
Bards -<br>
Never been jumped by a bard, but I hear if they know what they're doing they can be hard. They are fast as greased lighting, and over time can do plenty of damage to you. Generally if you run from them (even though they can easily follow you) you will have ample time to get somewhere safe or pull the plug before their spells have done too much damage.<br>
<br>
Rangers -<br>
Chances are these guys are going to be twinked with some yaks or other fast 1h slashers. Watch out for snare, but other then that treat them like a warrior. Might want some slower weapons if they have damage shields.<br>
<br>
<br>
